tspan.tspan: No! You can’t just call them all URLs! There are
differences between URLs, URNs, and URIs,
which all help in locating a resource on the
Internet. URN and URL are subsets of URI. The
URL gives the location or the address of the
resource while the URN gives the name of the
specific resource but not necessarily the location!
They are not the same! The URN describes the
identity of an item while the URL links a webpage,
a component of a web page, or a program on a
web page with the help of accessing methods like
protocols. The URI is used to distinguish one
resource from the other no matter the method
